President Trump and Chancellor Merkel held a joint press conference at the White House. They discussed a range of topics including trade, NATO, immigration, and the fight against terrorism. Trump reiterated his support for NATO but emphasized the need for all member nations to pay their fair share for defense. Merkel expressed Germany's commitment to increase defense spending and work towards contributing at least 2 percent of GDP. They also discussed the conflict in Ukraine and the importance of finding a peaceful solution. On trade, both leaders expressed their desire for fair and reciprocal trade policies. Trump mentioned that the US has been treated unfairly in trade deals and wants to bring jobs back to the country. Merkel highlighted the benefits of trade agreements and the importance of mutual benefits for both sides.